At 09:08 AM 4/11/2010, you wrote:
"I was going to do a little bit of tuning in the next few days to at 
least richen it up a hair so it's not bucking quite as much.  I just 
don't want to get it too close to stoich because then like you said a 
while back, I run the risk of one cylinder going hotter than the 
others and frying my heads, and I have no way of monitoring it. Plus, 
I'm a bit paranoid about these heads because I spent a pretty penny on them.."

You will find that a lean mix increases heat, not rich. I would want 
not less than 3.0% O2 at idle to insure not too lean/hot.
